# Checkbox

A IDS checkbox is an input option that represents a setting or value with an on, off, or mixed choice.
A check mark within the checkbox indicates that the setting is selected or checked.
Checkboxes in a group are non-exclusive options; more than one checkbox in a group can be checked at any given time.

## Installation & Import

```bash
yarn add @ids-ts/checkbox
```

```tsx
import { Checkbox, CheckboxGroup } from '@ids-ts/checkbox';
```

## Props API

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `assignInputRef` | `(c: HTMLInputElement | null) => void` | No | A function to get reference to input element. |
| `checked` | `boolean` | No | Specifies whether the checkbox is checked. |
| `children` | `ReactNode | string` | No | The Checkbox label. |
| `description` | `ReactNode | string` | No | * Description text below the label |
| `defaultChecked` | `boolean` | No | Initial checked state (uncontrolled). |
| `disabled` | `boolean` | No | - |
| `indeterminate` | `boolean` | No | - |
| `name` | `string` | No | a name assign to the checkbox input |
| `onBlur` | `FocusEventHandler<HTMLInputElement>` | No | Callback function that is fired when a Checkbox has been blurred. |
| `onChange` | `CheckboxOnChangeType` | No | Callback function with customize event object that is fired when a Checkbox has been checked. |
| `onClick` | `MouseEventHandler<HTMLInputElement>` | No | Callback function that is fired when a Checkbox has been clicked. |
| `onFocus` | `FocusEventHandler<HTMLInputElement>` | No | Callback function that is fired when a Checkbox has been focused. |
| `size` | `'small' | 'medium'` | No | - |
| `tabIndex` | `number` | No | tab-index assign to the checkbox input. |
| `validationMessage` | `string` | No | Validation Message. |
| `InlineValidationMessage` | `'error', 'warning', 'success', 'invalid', 'info...` | Yes | - |
| `value` | `string` | No | Checkbox current value. |
| `e` | `CheckboxOnChangeEventType): void` | Yes | - |
| `target` | `{ checked: boolean; value: string }` | Yes | Modified event target with check value. |

